-- Russian Ministry Offers Exploration Rights to 58 Oil, Gas Fields
-- B y   J a k e   R u d n i t s k y
-- 2012-02-13T15:09:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-13/russian-ministry-offers-exploration-rights-to-58-oil-gas-fields.html
Russia ’s subsoil agency Rosnedra is
accepting applications for the rights to explore 58 prospective
oil and gas fields until April 12, according to  information  on
the Natural Resources Ministry’s website posted today.  The largest oil field being offered is in the Krasnoyarsk
territory with prospective D1 and D2 resources of 83 million
metric tons of crude, or 608 million barrels, according to
Russia’s classification system.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jake Rudnitsky in Moscow at 
 jrudnitsky@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
